    "summary": "Christina Peristeridou is assistant professor of criminal law & procedure at Maastricht University. She has wide expertise covering both substantive and procedural law, EU and national law. Currently she focuses on comparative criminal procedure, virtual justice and pre-trial detention. She has published extensively on these topics. Previously she published on the principle of legality and EU criminal law. She is a trained lawyer called to the Bar of Thessaloniki since 2008.  She is founder and co-chair of Female Empowerment Maastricht University (FEM) promoting equity in academia. She coordinates and teaches BA and MA courses on criminal procedure and EU criminal law. \n\nShe holds a PhD from Maastricht in EU criminal law, a LLM (cum laude) in EU law from Tilburg University and a Bachelors degree in Law from Aristotle University of Thessaloniki, Greece.  She has received additional training in legal philosophy from the European University Institute (Florence), in European Criminal Law from the Siracusa Institute (Italy) and she is trained also in Human Rights law from the University of Macedonia, in Thessaloniki. ",
